[ASSISTANT] Obtaining the available video tracks depends on the specific media source or track information you are using. I'll provide you with a couple of examples to give you an idea of how to retrieve video tracks from different sources.

1. From MediaSource:
If you are using a `MediaSource` implementation, such as `ProgressiveMediaSource`, `DashMediaSource`, or `HlsMediaSource`, you can retrieve the video tracks using the `getTrackGroups()` method.

Here's an example:
```kotlin
val mediaSource: MediaSource = // Your media source
val videoTracks: MutableList<Format> = mutableListOf()

val trackGroups: TrackGroupArray = mediaSource.getTrackGroups()
for (i in 0 until trackGroups.length) {
    val trackGroup: TrackGroup = trackGroups.get(i)
    for (j in 0 until trackGroup.length) {
        val format: Format = trackGroup.getFormat(j)
        if (format.sampleMimeType?.startsWith("video/") == true) {
            videoTracks.add(format)
        }
    }
}

// Now you have the available video tracks in the videoTracks list
```

2. From TrackSelectorResult:
If you already have a `TrackSelector` set up and have performed track selection, you can retrieve the selected video tracks from the `TrackSelectorResult` obtained from the `trackSelector.getCurrentMappedTrackInfo()`.

Here's an example:
```kotlin
val trackSelectorResult: TrackSelectorResult = // Your TrackSelectorResult
val videoTracks: MutableList<Format> = mutableListOf()

val mappedTrackInfo: TrackSelectorResult.MappedTrackInfo = trackSelectorResult.getMappedTrackInfo()
for (i in 0 until mappedTrackInfo.rendererCount) {
    val trackGroups: TrackGroupArray = mappedTrackInfo.getTrackGroups(i)
    for (j in 0 until trackGroups.length) {
        val trackGroup: TrackGroup = trackGroups.get(j)
        for (k in 0 until trackGroup.length) {
            val format: Format = trackGroup.getFormat(k)
            if (format.sampleMimeType?.startsWith("video/") == true) {
                videoTracks.add(format)
            }
        }
    }
}

// Now you have the available video tracks in the videoTracks list
```

These examples assume that you are working with `Format` objects representing the video tracks. Adjust the code based on the specific format or track object used by your media source or track information.

Remember to replace the comments (`// Your media source`) with the appropriate instances or references to your media source or track selector result.

